FCH

Then I saw the heavens opened and the Son of Man sitting at the right hand of YHWH in glory. And all the righteous rejoiced and sang praises to YHWH. And the Lord said to me: “This is the place of rest for the righteous. But for the sinners there is no rest, but eternal fire and torment.” Then the vision ended and Peter returned to his companions and told them all that he had seen.
And the Lord said: “Go now and proclaim this to the world, that men may repent and be saved from the coming judgment.” Then the heavens closed and the vision ended.
Then the righteous shone like the sun in the kingdom of their Father. And the sinners wept and gnashed their teeth in the outer darkness. Then the Lord commanded that the vision be sealed until the last days. And Peter awoke from the vision and gave thanks to YHWH.
And I saw the righteous entering into eternal life and the sinners being cast into the place of torment. Then the Lord Jesus the Anointed said to me: “This is the revelation which you must proclaim to the world.”
Then the Lord commanded the angels to take the righteous into the eternal kingdom and to cast the sinners into the lake of fire. And the vision ended.
Then I Peter saw the Son of Man coming in glory with all His angels and sitting upon the throne of His glory. And the books were opened and the dead were judged according to their deeds.

